benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/admin/queues - Get queues entries

covered: Valid requests: Many scenarios (TC01-TC12, TC23, TC10) cover successful 200 responses for default behavior, individual filters (accountId, queueName, serviceName, date range), combined filters, and partial/extra parameters.
Default flags and backward compatibility: TC01 and TC22 verify default behavior for withHistory, withInProcessing, withBusEvents, withNotifications and legacy clients omitting new params.
Query-parameter validation and error handling: TC13 (invalid accountId -> 400), TC14 (account not found -> 404), TC25 (malformed date -> 400) cover key validation/error cases.
Flags toggle and regression: TC06-TC09 and regression TC21 validate that flags (withHistory, withInProcessing, withBusEvents, withNotifications) correctly include/exclude data.
Error and resilience coverage: TC15 (401), TC16 (503), TC19 (504), TC30 (500) provide broad error-path coverage.
Security and input sanitation: TC17 (injection) and TC26 (XSS) address common attack vectors for query parameters.
Performance and scale: TC18 (large dataset performance) checks response time expectations; TC20 covers concurrent request correctness.
Empty/no-match handling: TC11 and TC29 verify empty-result behavior (200 with empty body).
Documentation and error schema intent: TC28 addresses that error messages should be descriptive and follow a consistent schema.
Content-Type produced: TC01 asserts application/octet-stream for successful responses (acceptance criteria verified at least once).
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover pagination (page/limit/offset or next/prev links). If the API uses streaming instead of pagination, tests should explicitly assert streaming behavior; this is currently not covered.
Rate limiting / throttling: No tests validate rate-limit behavior (e.g., triggering 429, Retry-After header) under rapid/repeated requests.
Caching behavior: No scenarios check caching headers or conditional GETs (ETag, Cache-Control, Last-Modified, 304 responses).
Boolean parameter validation: Missing tests for invalid boolean values (e.g., withHistory=foo) and expected 400 responses.
Date-range edge cases: No tests for minDate > maxDate or boundary validation beyond the single-range and min/max limits.

Response format & streaming details: Apart from one content-type assertion, tests do not validate serialization format of the octet-stream, chunked/stream transfer behavior, Content-Length/Transfer-Encoding, or content integrity of the serialized stream.
Authorization nuance: 401 is covered, but 403/role-based access control or token-scope failures are not tested.
Error payload schema enforcement: TC28 exists but there are no strict JSON schema assertions across all error status codes to ensure consistent error payload fields/structure.
Accept header / content negotiation: No tests for how Accept header variations are handled (e.g., client requests other media types).
recommendations: Add pagination tests if the endpoint supports it: verify page/limit parameters, limits, and next/prev links. If the endpoint streams data instead, add tests that validate streaming behavior, chunk integrity, and total record counts.
Implement rate-limiting tests that fire many requests in a short timeframe to validate 429 responses and Retry-After header semantics and ensure graceful client backoff.
Add caching tests: assert presence and correctness of Cache-Control/ETag/Last-Modified headers and verify conditional GET behavior (304 Not Modified) where applicable.
Add strict input validation tests for boolean flags (invalid types), and additional date validation tests (minDate > maxDate, boundary values, timezone/format variations).

Standardize and assert response serialization for application/octet-stream: include tests that deserialize/parse the octet-stream, validate record formats, and check chunked transfer behavior and Content-Length/Transfer-Encoding for large responses.
Cover authorization nuances: add 403 tests and role/token-scope tests to ensure only authorized admin roles can access the endpoint.
Formalize error-schema tests: adopt JSON schema checks for error payloads (400/401/403/404/429/500/503/504) to ensure consistent fields and descriptive messages.
Add Accept header/content-negotiation tests and validate server behavior when clients request unsupported media types.
If pagination is intentionally omitted, document that decision and add explicit tests asserting streaming-only behavior (and why pagination is not applicable).
